  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\nAfter updating the elasticsearch container in the fluentd-elasticsearch addon to use version 5.4.0-1, the following error occurs:\r\n\r\n```\r\nkubectl -n monitoring logs elasticsearch-logging-713280597-2l0ct\r\nsysctl: error setting key 'vm.max_map_count': Read-only file system\r\n```\r\n\r\nI believe this is caused by [this line](https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/cluster/addons/fluentd-elasticsearch/es-image/run.sh#L17), which was introduced in the latest commit. It appears that this happens because /sys is mounted read-only in containers. However, it does seem to be important to running elasticsearch (see https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/vm-max-map-count.html).\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nElasticsearch to start normally.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\nModify the container version in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/cluster/addons/fluentd-elasticsearch/es-controller.yaml to be 5.4.0-1 and install the addon.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n\r\n```\r\nkubectl version\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"7\", GitVersion:\"v1.7.2\", GitCommit:\"922a86cfcd65915a9b2f69f3f193b8907d741d9c\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2017-07-21T08:23:22Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.8.3\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\nServer Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"7\", GitVersion:\"v1.7.2\", GitCommit:\"922a86cfcd65915a9b2f69f3f193b8907d741d9c\", GitTreeState:\"clean\", BuildDate:\"2017-07-21T08:08:00Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.8.3\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\nIssue occurs on Kubernetes running on Ubuntu Xenial VirtualBox VMs.",
